b'' b"i'd like to know if there is any system (cpu hd array framebuffer)" b'which can play and record hdtv quality moving picture in realtime.' b'' b'hdtv has about 6mb/frame, so recording/playing moving picture will need' b"about 180mb/sec bandwidth. i'm thinking to treat the raw data.. not" b'compressed.' b'' b"actually, for digital hdtv systems that's far higher bandwidth than" b"you need, unless there's some reason you must work in fully-uncompressed" b'hdtv. also, my calculations is that each frame should be well under 6mb,' b'even using bits/pixel (which is more bits than you actually need or' b"18 should be enough for a moving picture). 1600x1100x16bits is 3.5mb (i'm" b"guessing at hdtv resolution it may be a bit wider than i'm fairly" b'sure of the number for most of the digital proposals).' b'' b'i hope you have a very fast memory system as well 180mb/s while' b'displaying will require a heavily interleaved vram system.' b'' b"unless you have a _very_ compelling reason, i'd advise trying to use" b"at least somewhat compressed data. you don't have to go to full compression" b'to get to a level where the data io requirements are much cheaper and easier' b'to deal with.' b'' b'--' b'gnu emacs is a lisp operating system disguised as a word processor.' b'- doug mohney, in comp.arch' b'' b'randell jesup, jack-of-quite-a-few-trades, commodore engineering.' b'disclaimer: nothing i say is anything other than my personal opinion.' 